Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Kosovo. The authorities in Kosovo have introduced a number of strict measures to limit the spread of the virus.
Entry and borders
All flights into Kosovo have been cancelled and flights departing are likely to be severely disrupted, if not cancelled.
Keep up to date with information from your tour operator, transport or accommodation provider on the impact on any existing travel plans.
Land borders are closed to entry by non-Kosovo citizens. A number of border crossings with neighbouring countries are closed for passenger traffic, and neighbouring countries have also placed restrictions on international travel. You should check FCO travel advice for the relevant country before attempting to cross a border.
Local measures
All schools, cafes, bars, restaurants and shopping centres have been closed. Food stores and pharmacies remain open.
Public transport has been restricted.
There are restrictions on large public gatherings. A number of events in Kosovo in the coming weeks and months have been cancelled.
Further information
The authorities in Kosovo have set up an online platform with basic information and advice available in English, as well as the facility to speak to a medical professional. There is a local Emergency Hotline for people who think they may have coronavirus. The number is 038 200 80 800.
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
